  <section>
    <h2>What is Calculus?</h2>
    <p>Calculus is like magic math! It helps us understand how things change, like how fast you're running, or how high a rocket goes.</p>

    <h2>Meet Derivatives!</h2>
    <p>Derivatives tell us how fast something is changing. Imagine you're riding your bike. The derivative tells you how fast you're going every second!</p>
    <div class="example">
      üõ¥ If you go 10 meters in 1 second, your speed (derivative) is 10 meters/second!
    </div>

    <h2>Meet Integrals!</h2>
    <p>Integrals are like adding up little pieces. They help us find how much space is under a curve or how far you've traveled.</p>
    <div class="example">
      üç∞ Imagine you eat a cake slice by slice. An integral adds all the slices to find out how much cake you've eaten!
    </div>

